## Worktree

You are operating in a git worktree (created by `flt spawn` — your branch
is named after you). Two consequences:

- Pushing from here goes to a per-agent branch, never directly to `main`.
  Don't `git push origin main` or rebase the integration branch from inside
  the worktree.
- `flt kill <you>` removes this worktree. If you produce diffs or files you
  want to keep outside the normal commit/PR flow, copy them out before kill
  (handoffs in `$FLT_RUN_DIR/handoffs/` survive teardown; loose files in
  the worktree do not).
